It has been determined that there is no statistically significant difference in the mass of eye lenses processed using the standard and the applied modified methods in both age categories. Therefore, with the application of the first and third modified methods, the time required for obtaining the analyses is 5 days, with the fixation duration in formalin being 48 hours. In most of the available studies that dealt with determining the age of hares, the fixation time was longer and ranged from 3 days (

